#### 3. CLI Commands for Date References

When needing current date information, use these commands:
```bash
# Get current date in ISO format
date -u +"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ"

# Get current quarter info
date +"%Y Q$((($(date +%-m)-1)/3+1))"

# Get relative dates for examples
date -u -d "1 day ago" +"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ"
date -u -d "1 week ago" +"%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ"
```

